ONE TIME SHE HAD ME DO

08:53.658 --> 08:56.577
HER WHOLE SCIENCE FAIR PROJECT.

08:56.619 --> 08:58.579
DADDY! (giggles)

08:58.621 --> 09:00.415
I HAVE TO TAKE

08:58.621 --> 09:00.415
ANOTHER SHOWER.

09:00.457 --> 09:01.582
OKAY, SCOTT,

09:01.624 --> 09:03.584
YOU'RE A GREAT GUY

09:01.624 --> 09:03.584
WITH AMAZING LEGS,

09:03.626 --> 09:06.254
BUT I'M SORRY. I'M NOT

09:03.626 --> 09:06.254
DATING MY ROOMMATE'S DAD,

09:06.296 --> 09:08.589
SO SCOOCH, OKAY?

09:08.631 --> 09:09.590
HERE'S THE DOOR.

09:09.632 --> 09:11.592
YOU'RE THE DAD.

09:11.634 --> 09:14.012
HALF OF CHLOE

09:11.634 --> 09:14.012
CAME FROM YOU.

09:14.054 --> 09:18.599
MY COMPLIMENTS

09:14.054 --> 09:18.599
TO THE CHEF.

09:18.641 --> 09:22.603
COMPLIMENT THE CHEF OUTSIDE.

09:18.641 --> 09:22.603
THANK YOU.

09:22.645 --> 09:25.315
(horn blares)

09:25.357 --> 09:26.983
SO WHEN I BEGIN TO INHABIT

09:25.357 --> 09:26.983
A CHARACTER,

09:27.025 --> 09:29.610
I ASK MYSELF, "WHO IS HE?

09:27.025 --> 09:29.610
WHAT DOES HE WANT?

09:29.652 --> 09:31.029
AND WHAT IS HE GONNA DO

09:29.652 --> 09:31.029
IF HE DOESN'T GET IT?"

09:31.071 --> 09:33.490
NOW LET'S TALK ABOUT HOW THIS

09:31.071 --> 09:33.490
WOULD IMPACT OUR APPROACH

09:33.532 --> 09:35.200
TO THE ROLE OF HAMLET.

09:35.242 --> 09:36.826
WAS IT FUN KISSING

09:35.242 --> 09:36.826
KATIE HOLMES?

09:36.868 --> 09:39.287
(students chuckle)

09:36.868 --> 09:39.287
LET'S TRY AND STAY FOCUSED

09:36.868 --> 09:39.287
ON THE TASK AT HAND HERE--

09:39.329 --> 09:41.622
DID ANYONE HAVE

09:39.329 --> 09:41.622
AN EATING DISORDER?

09:39.329 --> 09:41.622
OKAY, WE'RE NOT HERE TO TALK

09:39.329 --> 09:41.622
ABOUT "DAWSON'S CREEK."

09:41.664 --> 09:43.624
WE'RE HERE TO EXPLORE

09:41.664 --> 09:43.624
THE CRAFT OF ACTING--

09:43.666 --> 09:44.625
DO THE MONOLOGUE

09:43.666 --> 09:44.625
FROM THE EPISODE

09:44.667 --> 09:46.627
WHERE YOU REALIZE

09:44.667 --> 09:46.627
YOU LOVE JOEY!

09:46.669 --> 09:47.712
(students chanting)

09:46.669 --> 09:47.712
DO IT! DO IT!

09:47.754 --> 09:50.715
ALL RIGHT. IN "HAMLET,"

09:47.754 --> 09:50.715
WHAT DO WE HAVE?

09:50.757 --> 09:53.927
WE HAVE A PRINCE WITH A PROB--

09:50.757 --> 09:53.927
SERIOUSLY?!

09:50.757 --> 09:53.927
(chanting continues)

09:53.968 --> 09:55.678
DO IT, DO IT, DO IT!

09:53.968 --> 09:55.678
YOU GUYS DON'T WANNA LEARN

09:53.968 --> 09:55.678
ABOUT ACTING?

09:55.720 --> 09:58.639
ALL YOU WANNA HEAR IS, "JOEY,

09:55.720 --> 09:58.639
GOD, I-I MEAN, THIS IS ALL NEW.

09:58.681 --> 10:01.642
"WE SHOULD TALK ABOUT THIS.

09:58.681 --> 10:01.642
BUT NO MATTER WHAT HAPPENS,

10:01.684 --> 10:03.270
"WE CAN'T GO BACK

10:01.684 --> 10:03.270
TO THE WAY THINGS WERE.

10:03.311 --> 10:05.813
JOEY, DON'T WALK AWAY

10:03.311 --> 10:05.813
FROM THIS."

10:05.855 --> 10:07.566
(woman whimpers)

10:07.607 --> 10:09.650
(applause)

10:07.607 --> 10:09.650
(woman) OHH.

10:09.692 --> 10:10.818
WHAT?

10:10.860 --> 10:12.487
(laughter)

10:12.529 --> 10:14.448
THE CREEK!

10:14.489 --> 10:16.699
(woman)

10:14.489 --> 10:16.699
HAVE MY BABY, DAWSON!

10:16.741 --> 10:18.659
(horn honks)

10:18.701 --> 10:20.495
I DON'T NORMALLY

10:18.701 --> 10:20.495
MOVE THAT FAST,

10:20.537 --> 10:22.663
BUT I REALLY FELT

10:20.537 --> 10:22.663
A CONNECTION WITH SCOTT,

10:22.705 --> 10:24.665
AND HE FIT PERFECTLY

10:22.705 --> 10:24.665
INTO MY LIFE PLAN,

10:24.707 --> 10:26.334
AND I TOUCHED IT THROUGH

10:24.707 --> 10:26.334
BIKE SHORTS, AND I THINK THAT--

10:26.376 --> 10:28.503
YIKES.

10:26.376 --> 10:28.503
(door bells jingle)

10:28.545 --> 10:30.338
I HAVE  NOTHING  TO SAY

10:28.545 --> 10:30.338
TO YOU.

10:30.380 --> 10:32.673
JUNE, GOD, I MEAN,

10:30.380 --> 10:32.673
THIS IS ALL NEW.

10:32.715 --> 10:34.509
WE SHOULD TALK ABOUT IT.

10:34.551 --> 10:35.676
NO MATTER WHAT HAPPENS,

10:34.551 --> 10:35.676
WE CAN'T GO BACK

10:35.718 --> 10:37.678
TO THE WAY THINGS WERE.

10:35.718 --> 10:37.678
JUNE, DON'T WALK AWAY--

10:37.720 --> 10:39.598
THAT'S THE SPEECH

10:37.720 --> 10:39.598
FROM SEASON 1, EPISODE 12

10:39.639 --> 10:41.724
OF "DAWSON'S CREEK,"

10:39.639 --> 10:41.724
I'VE SEEN THEM ALL.

10:41.766 --> 10:43.684
(pounds counter)

10:41.766 --> 10:43.684
DAMN IT! SMALL TOWN GIRL.

10:43.726 --> 10:46.687
WHAT DO YOU WANT?

10:43.726 --> 10:46.687
LOOK, IF YOU DON'T

10:43.726 --> 10:46.687
WANNA DATE MY DAD

10:46.729 --> 10:49.732
BECAUSE HE'S MY DAD, FINE.

10:46.729 --> 10:49.732
IT'S YOUR LOSS.

10:49.774 --> 10:51.359
BUT HE'S REALLY UPSET.

10:51.401 --> 10:54.695
SO CAN YOU AT LEAST

10:51.401 --> 10:54.695
TALK TO HIM?

10:54.737 --> 10:56.948
DAD? STOP DUCKING

10:54.737 --> 10:56.948
BEHIND A CHUBBO.

10:56.990 --> 10:59.909
SORRY. SORRY.

10:59.951 --> 11:01.035
RUNS IN THE FAMILY.

11:02.745 --> 11:03.704
HEY.

11:03.746 --> 11:05.165
HEY.

11:06.791 --> 11:08.709
SEEMS LIKE

11:06.791 --> 11:08.709
A REAL MESSED UP SITUATION.

11:08.751 --> 11:11.712
YEAH, NO ONE'S TO BLAME,

11:08.751 --> 11:11.712
THOUGH, SO THAT'S GOOD.

11:11.754 --> 11:13.714
SO WHAT'S YOUR STORY?

11:11.754 --> 11:13.714
WHO ARE YOU?

11:13.756 --> 11:17.760
WELL, I'M MARK.

11:13.756 --> 11:17.760
I WORK HERE WITH JUNE?

11:17.802 --> 11:19.720
WE'VE MET SEVERAL TIMES

11:17.802 --> 11:19.720
BEFORE. I DON'T--

11:17.802 --> 11:19.720
(door bells jingle)

11:19.762 --> 11:21.764
STUPID N.Y.U. KIDS.

11:21.806 --> 11:23.600
I'M MORE THAN JUST

11:21.806 --> 11:23.600
ONE ROLE.

11:23.642 --> 11:25.101
I WAS THE ORIGINAL GAVROCHE

11:23.642 --> 11:25.101
IN "LES MIS."

11:25.143 --> 11:26.727
I WAS IN KE$HA'S "BLOW" VIDEO.

11:26.769 --> 11:29.523
I WAS IN AN ALL-WHITE PRODUCTION

11:26.769 --> 11:29.523
OF "RAISIN IN THE SUN."

11:29.564 --> 11:30.731
THAT WAS A LONG NIGHT.

11:30.773 --> 11:31.732
I'M TIRED OF PEOPLE

11:30.773 --> 11:31.732
TRYING TO PIGEONHOLE ME.

11:31.774 --> 11:33.734
YOU KNOW, THEY WANNA

11:31.774 --> 11:33.734
PUT ME IN A BOX.

11:33.776 --> 11:35.736
I KNOW WHAT YOU MEAN, MAN.

11:35.778 --> 11:36.821
I GOT AN MBA FROM STANFORD

11:36.863 --> 11:38.739
AND TWO YEARS

11:36.863 --> 11:38.739
AT A TOP MORTGAGE FIRM,

11:38.781 --> 11:40.741
BUT PEOPLE JUST SEE ME

11:38.781 --> 11:40.741
AS A DUDE WHO MAKES COFFEE.

11:40.783 --> 11:42.827
DO I GET DISCOURAGED?

11:40.783 --> 11:42.827
YEAH, SOMETIMES.

11:42.869 --> 11:45.622
BUT YOU GUYS KNOW ME.

11:42.869 --> 11:45.622
NEVER GONNA GIVE UP.

11:47.248 --> 11:49.668
WHO IS THIS GUY?

11:47.248 --> 11:49.668
WHAT'S HIS STORY?

11:47.248 --> 11:49.668
NO IDEA.

11:49.708 --> 11:52.546
(mutters)

11:49.708 --> 11:52.546
UH... ALL RIGHT.

11:52.587 --> 11:54.130
CHLOE SAID YOU WEREN'T

11:52.587 --> 11:54.130
INTERESTED IN PURSUING THIS,

11:54.172 --> 11:57.258
AND I RESPECT THAT,

11:54.172 --> 11:57.258
BUT GETTING TO KNOW YOU WAS--

11:57.300 --> 11:59.052
AMAZING. I KNOW.

11:57.300 --> 11:59.052
IT'S JUST SO--

11:59.093 --> 12:01.388
COMPLICATED. I GET IT.

12:01.429 --> 12:04.349
I-I JUST--I WANTED YOU

12:01.429 --> 12:04.349
TO HAVE THIS.

12:04.391 --> 12:07.768
IS THAT...

12:04.391 --> 12:07.768
McGRUFF THE CRIME DOG?

12:07.810 --> 12:09.688
I REMEMBER YOU SAID HOW MUCH

12:07.810 --> 12:09.688
YOU LOVED HIM.

12:09.728 --> 12:11.481
YOUR PARENTS WERE

12:09.728 --> 12:11.481
ARGUING A LOT THAT FALL,

12:11.523 --> 12:13.274
AND HE MADE YOU FEEL SAFE.

12:13.316 --> 12:16.027
OH, HEY, A STUFFED ANIMAL

12:13.316 --> 12:16.027
FROM A MUCH OLDER MAN.

12:16.069 --> 12:18.613
NOTHING WEIRD ABOUT THAT.

12:18.655 --> 12:19.864
TOOK ME ALL DAY TO FIND ONE.

12:18.655 --> 12:19.864
WASN'T EASY,

12:19.906 --> 12:22.783
BUT ONCE I SET MY MIND

12:19.906 --> 12:22.783
ON SOMETHING...

12:22.825 --> 12:23.993
I DON'T GIVE UP.

12:25.828 --> 12:32.793
I'M IN A SCOTT-McGRUFF SANDWICH,

12:25.828 --> 12:32.793
AND I'VE NEVER FELT SAFER.

12:32.835 --> 12:35.213
(chuckles)

12:35.255 --> 12:39.300
IN 11 YEARS, STEVEN NEVER

12:35.255 --> 12:39.300
GOT ME A PRESENT LIKE THIS.

12:39.342 --> 12:42.803
HE WAS ALWAYS TOO BUSY

12:39.342 --> 12:42.803
FOCUSING ON HIS WORK

12:42.845 --> 12:44.805
OR HIS CHEATING.

12:44.847 --> 12:46.807
BUT MAYBE THAT RELATIONSHIP

12:44.847 --> 12:46.807
WASN'T MEANT TO BE.

12:46.849 --> 12:49.977
MAYBE I WAS SUPPOSED TO GO

12:46.849 --> 12:49.977
THROUGH ALL OF THAT WITH STEVEN

12:50.019 --> 12:51.812
JUST SO THAT I COULD

12:50.019 --> 12:51.812
MEET YOU.

12:51.854 --> 12:55.816
THIS MIGHT SOUND CHEESY, BUT I

12:51.854 --> 12:55.816
THINK YOU MIGHT BE MY SOUL MATE.

12:55.858 --> 12:57.736
I LIKE CHEESY.

12:58.861 --> 13:02.031
(high-pitched voice)

12:58.861 --> 13:02.031
I LIKE CHEESY, TOO!

13:02.073 --> 13:04.325
THAT'S A VERY GOOD McGRUFF

13:02.073 --> 13:04.325
IMPERSONATION.

13:04.367 --> 13:06.827
(laughs)

13:07.954 --> 13:10.831
♪ BA-DA-DA-DA-DA-BA, BA-DA-BA ♪

13:10.873 --> 13:12.833
CHLOE.

13:12.875 --> 13:14.335
OH, YOU WERE SO RIGHT.

13:14.377 --> 13:16.337
IT DOESN'T MATTER

13:14.377 --> 13:16.337
THE AGE DIFFERENCE

13:16.379 --> 13:17.838
OR HOW WE MET.

13:17.880 --> 13:19.466
ALL THAT MATTERS

13:17.880 --> 13:19.466
IS THAT HE'S A GREAT GUY,

13:19.507 --> 13:22.302
AND WE HAVE

13:19.507 --> 13:22.302
A REALLY NICE CONNECTION.

13:22.343 --> 13:25.430
(sighs) I'M SO SORRY

13:22.343 --> 13:25.430
THAT I DIDN'T TRUST YOU.

13:25.472 --> 13:28.057
THANK YOU.

13:25.472 --> 13:28.057
APOLOGY ACCEPTED.

13:29.517 --> 13:30.851
JUNE, THIS IS MY MOM.

13:30.893 --> 13:34.314
SHE'S REALLY UPSET. SHE THINKS

13:30.893 --> 13:34.314
MY DAD IS CHEATING ON HER.

13:37.191 --> 13:38.526
(sighs)

13:38.568 --> 13:41.529
IT'S SO GOOD TO MEET YOU,

13:38.568 --> 13:41.529
HONEY.

13:41.571 --> 13:45.366
NOW BEND DOWN

13:41.571 --> 13:45.366
AND GIVE ME A HUG.

13:45.408 --> 13:46.409
(door closes)

13:52.540 --> 13:53.583
(clenched teeth)

13:52.540 --> 13:53.583
I THOUGHT YOU TOLD ME

13:53.625 --> 13:55.876
THAT YOUR PARENTS

13:53.625 --> 13:55.876
WERE SEPARATED.

13:55.918 --> 13:57.462
THAT'S A LOOSE TERM.

13:57.504 --> 14:00.256
FIVE DAYS AGO,

13:57.504 --> 14:00.256
WE AGREED TO TAKE SOME SPACE.

14:00.298 --> 14:02.467
I WENT TO VISIT GRANDMA

14:00.298 --> 14:02.467
IN SCOTTSDALE...

14:02.509 --> 14:05.345
(voice breaking) AND HE

14:02.509 --> 14:05.345
STARTED PORKING SOME WHORE.

14:05.386 --> 14:06.887
WELL, I DON'T KNOW THAT WE NEED

14:05.386 --> 14:06.887
TO CALL HER NAMES.

14:06.929 --> 14:09.349
MOM, YOU AND DAD

14:06.929 --> 14:09.349
FOUGHT ALL THE TIME.

14:09.390 --> 14:11.726
YOU'RE THE ONE WHO WANTED

14:09.390 --> 14:11.726
TO SEPARATE IN THE FIRST PLACE.

14:11.768 --> 14:12.893
YES, BUT A FEW DAYS APART

14:11.768 --> 14:12.893
MADE ME REALIZE

14:12.935 --> 14:14.312
I WANTED TO BE

14:12.935 --> 14:14.312
WITH  YOUR FATHER

14:14.354 --> 14:15.896
AND APPARENTLY

14:14.354 --> 14:15.896
MADE HIM REALIZE

14:15.938 --> 14:17.816
HE WANTED TO BE

14:15.938 --> 14:17.816
WILT CHAMBERLAIN.

14:17.856 --> 14:19.776
MOM, YOU KNOW WHAT?

14:17.856 --> 14:19.776
HE'S MOVED ON.

14:19.818 --> 14:20.901
GET OVER IT.

14:20.943 --> 14:23.904
CHLOE, CAN I SPEAK WITH YOU?

14:26.324 --> 14:27.534
(crying)

14:27.575 --> 14:28.909
(whispers) WHAT THE HELL?!

14:28.951 --> 14:30.203
DON'T FALL FOR IT.

14:28.951 --> 14:30.203
IT'S AN ACT.

14:30.244 --> 14:31.912
SHE'S A TOTAL DRAMA QUEEN.

14:31.954 --> 14:33.914
I THINK I'VE RUINED EVERYTHING!

14:33.956 --> 14:35.916
SEE? SHE WANTS US

14:33.956 --> 14:35.916
TO SAY "NO."

14:35.958 --> 14:36.917
(lowered voice)

14:35.958 --> 14:36.917
SHE'S SUCH A PIECE OF WORK.

14:36.959 --> 14:39.796
SHE SEEMS PRETTY SINCERE,

14:36.959 --> 14:39.796
AND BY THE WAY,

14:39.838 --> 14:41.589
SHE'S IN A WHEELCHAIR,

14:41.631 --> 14:43.007
WHICH IS WHY SHE WAS

14:41.631 --> 14:43.007
ADDICTED TO PAINKILLERS

14:43.049 --> 14:44.300
AND COULDN'T TAKE YOU

14:43.049 --> 14:44.300
ICE-SKATING

14:44.342 --> 14:45.926
OR HORSEBACK RIDING.

14:45.968 --> 14:48.179
LOOK, I DON'T KNOW IF SHE COULD

14:45.968 --> 14:48.179
OR SHE COULDN'T.

14:48.221 --> 14:50.306
ALL I KNOW

14:48.221 --> 14:50.306
IS THAT SHE DIDN'T.

14:50.348 --> 14:52.933
(chuckles)

14:52.975 --> 14:55.144
ISN'T IT OBVIOUS

14:52.975 --> 14:55.144
WHAT'S HAPPENING HERE?

14:55.186 --> 14:56.437
WHAT ARE YOU TALKING ABOUT?

14:56.479 --> 14:57.772
YOU'RE USING JUNE

14:56.479 --> 14:57.772
TO WORK OUT

14:57.814 --> 14:58.939
YOUR RESENTMENT

14:57.814 --> 14:58.939
TOWARDS YOUR MOTHER

14:58.981 --> 15:00.817
AND YOUR OBSESSION

14:58.981 --> 15:00.817
WITH YOUR FATHER.

15:00.859 --> 15:02.402
YOU PERCEIVED YOUR MOTHER

15:02.443 --> 15:04.111
AS NEGLECTFUL

15:02.443 --> 15:04.111
WHEN YOU WERE A CHILD?

15:04.153 --> 15:05.363
YEAH.

15:05.405 --> 15:06.406
SO WHEN SHE

15:05.405 --> 15:06.406
AND YOUR FATHER FOUGHT,

15:06.447 --> 15:07.782
YOU WOULD ALWAYS

15:06.447 --> 15:07.782
SIDE WITH HIM.

15:07.824 --> 15:09.158
I GUESS SO.

15:09.200 --> 15:10.410
WELL, NOW YOU'RE SUBCONSCIOUSLY

15:09.200 --> 15:10.410
USING JUNE AS A PAWN

15:10.451 --> 15:11.870
TO GET BACK AT YOUR MOTHER

15:11.911 --> 15:14.372
AND TO ALIGN YOURSELF

15:11.911 --> 15:14.372
MORE CLOSELY WITH YOUR DAD.

15:14.414 --> 15:16.332
WOW, I NEVER THOUGHT OF IT

15:14.414 --> 15:16.332
LIKE THAT.

15:16.374 --> 15:18.000
YOU NEVER THINK THINGS

15:16.374 --> 15:18.000
THROUGH, CHLOE.

15:18.042 --> 15:21.962
LIKE, DO YOU REALLY WANT JUNE

15:18.042 --> 15:21.962
TO BE YOUR NEW MOM?

15:22.004 --> 15:23.798
YOU'VE GOTTA BREAK UP

15:22.004 --> 15:23.798
WITH MY DAD.

15:23.840 --> 15:24.965
YA  THINK?

15:25.007 --> 15:26.801
ELI, THANK YOU SO MUCH.

15:26.843 --> 15:29.763
I GUESS I GOT A LOT GOING ON

15:26.843 --> 15:29.763
UNDERNEATH THE SURFACE.

15:29.804 --> 15:31.598
I'M LIKE A RIVER IN WINTER.

15:31.639 --> 15:34.267
YOU HAVE TO COME WITH ME

15:31.639 --> 15:34.267
TO BREAK UP WITH YOUR DAD.

15:31.639 --> 15:34.267
WHY?

15:34.308 --> 15:36.185
BECAUSE  YOU  ARE THE ONE

15:34.308 --> 15:36.185
THAT ORCHESTRATED

15:36.227 --> 15:37.562
THIS ENTIRE THING.

15:37.604 --> 15:38.855
HEY, I DIDN'T TAKE

15:37.604 --> 15:38.855
YOUR PANTY-HAMSTER

15:38.897 --> 15:40.899
AND PUT IT ON MY FATHER.

15:40.940 --> 15:44.569
THAT'S ANOTHER THING MY MOTHER

15:40.940 --> 15:44.569
NEVER GOT ME--A HAMSTER.

15:44.611 --> 15:46.070
FINE. LET'S GO.

15:47.822 --> 15:51.992
(indistinct conversations)

15:52.034 --> 15:52.993
(door closes, door bells jingle)

15:52.034 --> 15:52.993
DUDE, I HAD AN INSIGHT.

15:53.035 --> 15:54.662
JAMES, NOT NOW.

15:53.035 --> 15:54.662
I'M SLAMMED.

15:54.704 --> 15:56.372
WE JUST GOT A HUGE WAVE

15:54.704 --> 15:56.372
OF CUSTOMERS.

15:56.414 --> 15:58.040
YEAH, I KNOW.

15:56.414 --> 15:58.040
THEY CAME TO SEE ME.

15:58.082 --> 15:59.584
I TWEETED

15:58.082 --> 15:59.584
I WAS GONNA PERFORM HERE.

15:59.626 --> 16:01.586
IF PEOPLE ONLY SEE ME ONE WAY,

15:59.626 --> 16:01.586
IT'S UP TO  ME

16:01.628 --> 16:03.170
TO SHOW THEM

16:01.628 --> 16:03.170
I HAVE OTHER SWORDS IN MY BELT.

16:03.212 --> 16:04.714
NO, WE'RE NOT ZONED

16:03.212 --> 16:04.714
FOR THIS.

16:04.756 --> 16:06.507
PEOPLE ARE SITTING

